criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult patient, age> or = 18 years, both sexes;

          -  When using oxygen therapy by CNO2> 4 l / min, MR> or = 10 l / min of O2 or MV 50%, for
             maintain SpO2> 92%;

          -  f> 25irpm;

          -  Gasometric parameters (pre ELMO, up to 30 min before): pH> 7.35, PaO2> 70 mmHg, PaCO2
             between 35 and 45 mmHg, with PaO2 / FIO2 < or = 250, EtCO2 < or = 40 mmHg;

          -  RX or chest CT scan with bilateral parenchymal opacities from the last 24 hours.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Glasgow coma scale <13;

          -  Exacerbation of Asthma, COPD or other pneumopathies;

          -  Pathologies of the auditory canal;

          -  Clear signs of respiratory muscle fatigue (eg, movement paradoxical breathing, use of
             accessory muscles);

          -  Ineffective cough or inability to swallow;

          -  Use of nasoenteral or nasogastric tubes;

          -  Claustrophobia;

          -  Bloating, nausea or vomiting;

          -  Hemodynamic instability (SBP <90 mmHg or MBP <65 mmHg);

          -  Imminent risk of respiratory arrest.
